<h2 id="about">About <em>Sorghum bicolor</em> TX2783</h2>

<p><em>Sorghum bicolor</em> inbred line TX2783 (PI 656001) is a widely utilized pollinator parent with sugarcane aphid (SCA)-resistance, it was first bred for resistance to sorghum greenbug (<i>Schizaphis graminum</i>) and also exhibits high resistance to sugarcane aphid.
</p>

<!-- {about} -->
<!-- {assembly} --><a name="assembly"></a>
<h3 id="assembly">Assembly</h3>

<p>The genome assembly of <em>Sorghum TX2783</em> has been submitted for publication by Wang et al. Sequencing was done by the <a href="https://www.warelab.org/">Ware Lab</a>(USDA at CSHL) in collaboration with <a href="https://www.corteva.com/">Corteva Agriscience</a> using PacBio CLR technology to achieve 76X (reads N50=23.1 kb) coverage. The assembly effort generated contigs with N50 length of 25.6 Mb. In addition, Bionano molecules for Tx2783 yielded a genome map of 721.504 Mb with N50 lengths of 36.987 Mb. The chromosomes of the genome were constructed with hybrid scaffolds generated from BioNano genome maps. Most of the chromosomes were composed of two scaffolds.
</p>

<!-- {assembly} -->
<!-- {annotation} --><a name="annotation"></a>
<h3 id="genebuild">Annotation</h3>

<p>Gene calling was performed using a hybrid approach with de novo gene predictors and evidence-based methods (Wang et al, submitted), and then filtered based on annotation evidence distance (AED) scores, and homology to maize, brachypodium, rice, and Arabidopsis protein sequences. Ultimately, this approach generated a total of 29,612 protein-coding genes and 4,205 non-coding genes. 
</p>

<!-- {variation} --><a name="variation"></a>
<h3 id="variation">Variation</h3>

<p>This species currently has no variation database. However you can process your own variants using the <a href="http://ensembl.gramene.org/Sorghum_bicolor/Tools/VEP">Variant Effect Predictor (VEP)</a> in Gramene. 
</p>

